18. If both the catch block and the finally block throw exceptions, which one will be propagated to the caller, and why?
-->Answer:   
      The exception thrown by the finally block is propagated to the caller because the finally block executes after the catch block.
      
      Example
      public class Test {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
              try {
                  int a = 10 / 0;
              }
              catch (Exception e) {
                  throw new RuntimeException("Exception from catch");
              }
              finally {
                  throw new RuntimeException("Exception from finally");
              }
          }
      }
      Output
      Exception in thread "main"
      java.lang.RuntimeException: Exception from finally
      Explanation
      
      Execution order:
      
            try throws ArithmeticException.
            catch handles it and throws RuntimeException.
            finally executes and throws another RuntimeException.
            Exception from finally overrides the catch exception.




