20. What is a ClassCastException in Java? Write a program that demonstrates how this exception occurs and explain how to prevent it.
-->Answer
            
            A ClassCastException occurs when an object is cast to a type that it is not actually an instance of.
            
            Example
            class Animal {
            }
            
            class Dog extends Animal {
            }
            
            public class Test {
                public static void main(String[] args) {
            
                    Animal a = new Animal();
            
                    Dog d = (Dog) a; // Invalid cast
                }
            }
            Output
            Exception in thread "main"
            java.lang.ClassCastException
            Prevention
            
            Use instanceof before casting.
            
            if(a instanceof Dog) {
                Dog d = (Dog) a;
            }
            else {
                System.out.println("Cannot cast");
            }






